01:21.412 --> 01:23.114
He's all yours.

01:24.037 --> 01:28.534
Okay, Marion.
Chin down, no smile.

01:28.534 --> 01:31.908
You're sultry.
You eat men for lunch.

01:32.458 --> 01:34.038
Nice.

01:34.038 --> 01:36.716
Yes. Mm-hmm.

01:38.669 --> 01:40.546
Take a breather, sweetheart.

01:41.087 --> 01:43.009
I brought the final list.

01:43.009 --> 01:47.689
Uh, Marty Chapman agreed to emcee.

01:47.689 --> 01:49.182
I thought he wasn't available.

01:49.182 --> 01:50.937
No doesn't always mean no.

01:50.937 --> 01:52.976
I just need you to sign off on the budget.

01:52.976 --> 01:55.605
I'm bad with figures.
You know that.

01:56.686 --> 02:00.817
Harvey, all these famous people!

02:00.817 --> 02:02.945
You're a magician!

02:02.945 --> 02:04.745
It's only the beginning.

02:12.165 --> 02:14.955
I want full tox screens on every sample.

02:14.955 --> 02:18.169
Okay, folks. It's time to pick your pockets.

02:18.169 --> 02:20.919
So out with the checkbooks.
That's right.

02:20.919 --> 02:23.837
I want you to give till it hurts.

02:24.093 --> 02:27.714
Which for some of
you shouldn't take that long.

02:27.714 --> 02:30.639
She promised 35. We got 25.

02:30.639 --> 02:31.932
What's she trying to pull?

02:31.932 --> 02:34.516
Nothing, Stan.

02:34.516 --> 02:37.353
Just a misunderstanding.

02:37.353 --> 02:41.529
Now let's take a moment to say thank you
to our gorgeous hostess for the evening,

02:41.529 --> 02:43.531
Marion Whitney.

02:45.276 --> 02:46.945
Isn't she lovely?

02:46.945 --> 02:51.867
And she opened her beautiful home
for this worthy cause.

02:52.122 --> 02:53.700
But I would sincerely ask you all...

02:53.700 --> 02:56.663
- I need to see you in the library.
- Daniel, I'm in the middle of...

02:56.663 --> 02:59.710
There are two detectives here
about your husband.

02:59.710 --> 03:01.921
James? Tell them he passed away.

03:01.921 --> 03:05.507
That's why they're here.
They're saying he was murdered.

